metadata.name: Unicorn #125
metadata.description:
All of us have dreams, and everyone would like to meet a fairy, a genie, a wizard, or someone else who will make our dreams come true in a snap of a finger or with the wave of a wand. But we're the only ones who can do it. We are those magical unicorns, unique, inimitable, with our own qualities and magical abilities.
These unicorns are the visualization of our inner selves that makes our dreams come true. An embodiment of all the best with a huge positive magical power.

Twitter: @unicorn_nft_art
Web: https://unicorn-nft.web.app/

by @lucky26puch, @AgataBaranova17
Made in 2022

License: CC BY-NC 4.0

metadata.name: Minimum Viable Art {05:Audio} #62
metadata.description:
Series of studies focussed on fundamental generative design concepts and techniques. Audio is the study of web audio synthesis, musical scales, timbres, 2D grid edge detection and SDF shape building.

Please note that you must click on the artwork to hear the audio.

NFT License 2.0, https://www.nftlicense.org/

metadata.name: No strings attached #19
metadata.description:
Everything is connected. Enjoy it!

The project is written in vanilla Javascript.

The drawing is executed in a square at window resolution.

Press '2' to double the resolution. You can press again '2' to double once more;
Press '1' to get back at the window size.
Press 's' to save a png at the current resolution. You can also right click and 'save-as' to obtain the same result.


It uses 4 external packages, both licensed under MIT license:
* https://www.npmjs.com/package/delaunay-triangulate
* https://www.npmjs.com/package/simplex-noise
* https://www.npmjs.com/package/file-saver
* https://www.npmjs.com/package/alea

metadata.name: Comstractions #71
metadata.description: This collection explores the combination of abstract shapes and comic book styles. Several vintage comic palettes and bold outlines breathe life into abstract superheroes and villains, animals and buildings.

metadata.name: Gestalt #228
metadata.description:
"Gestalt" is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at The Ever-Evolving World of Art, Art Basel Hong-Kong, 2022

A flurry of many elements derived from my past (and future) strewn across a single canvas. As random as things seem, collectively time tends to reveal hints of order in the chaos. Sometimes, more is more.

Controls:
• Left-click/tap reassembles the piece with one less element each time
• 'R' reassembles the piece with all elements
• 'S' saves the output

“𝚃𝚑𝚎 𝚠𝚑𝚘𝚕𝚎 𝚒𝚜 𝚐𝚛𝚎𝚊𝚝𝚎𝚛 𝚝𝚑𝚊𝚗 𝚝𝚑𝚎 𝚜𝚞𝚖 𝚘𝚏 𝚒𝚝𝚜 𝚙𝚊𝚛𝚝𝚜.”

Made in p5js
Created May 2022
Artist: @Yazid
